# Command zsh-sage

## What does this command do:

Intelligent zsh autosuggestions with multi-signal ranking and confidence-colored ghost text

## Installed from

For Mac install using: brew tap UtsavMandal2022/zsh-sage && brew install zsh-sage

## Post-install setup

Add to ~/.zshrc (if not using Oh My Zsh):
  source $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh-sage/zsh-sage.plugin.zsh

Or add to Oh My Zsh plugins list:
  plugins=(git zsh-sage zsh-syntax-highlighting)

Import existing history on first run:
  zsh -ic '_sage_db_import_history'

Enable AI commands (requires Claude Code CLI):
  zsage ai

## Command path

For Mac run: /opt/homebrew/bin/zsage

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/UtsavMandal2022/zsh-sage

## Command options

### zsage CLI

zsage status     # current config, DB stats, active weights
zsage ai         # enable/disable AI commands (hm)
zsage stats      # top commands by frequency
zsage weights    # learned weights from your habits
zsage profile    # view ranking profile presets
zsage version    # show version
zsage help       # full usage info with color reference

### hm (AI commands — requires Claude Code)

hm find files larger than 1GB    # ask for a shell command in plain English
hm                                # suggest a fix for the last failed command

### Keybindings

Right arrow          Accept full suggestion
Option+Right         Accept word-by-word
Ctrl+Right           Accept word-by-word
Ctrl+N               Cycle through alternatives (up to 8 ranked suggestions)
Backspace            Clear and re-suggest

### Configuration (optional — defaults work without any of these)

export ZSH_SAGE_PROFILE="default"       # default | contextual | recent
export ZSH_SAGE_RECENCY_HALFLIFE=259200 # 3 days in seconds
export ZSH_SAGE_CYCLE_COUNT=8           # alternatives on Ctrl+N
export ZSH_SAGE_COLOR_HIGH=108          # high confidence color (256-color)
export ZSH_SAGE_COLOR_MED=245           # medium confidence color
export ZSH_SAGE_COLOR_LOW=240           # low confidence color
export ZSH_SAGE_CONFIDENCE_HIGH=0.70    # threshold for high confidence
export ZSH_SAGE_CONFIDENCE_LOW=0.30     # threshold for low confidence

### Uninstall

rm -rf $(brew --prefix)/share/zsh-sage
brew uninstall zsh-sage
rm -rf ~/.zsh-sage    # optional: remove command database
